  <description type="morphology">Plants straggling to bushy and erect. Stems glabrous. Leaf blades elliptic-lanceolate (rarely elliptic) to narrowly elliptic or linear-lanceolate, usually 2–3 cm, rarely longer, widest just below (rarely at) middle. Pedicels not reflexed in fruit (except in small, erect plants from nw North America). Flowers usually 5–6 mm diam.; sepals with midvein extending to near apex, lateral veins visible only at base, ovate to ovate-triangular, 2–3.3, to 0.5 times as long as capsule. Capsules dark brown, opaque, 3–4.5 mm, somewhat less than 2 times as long as broad. Seeds smooth or indistinctly rugulose. 2n = 52.</description>
